{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Persian}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=052|prev=Meowth|nextnum=054|next=Psyduck|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Persian}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Persian\n|jname=ペルシアン\n|jtranslit=Perushian\n|tmname=Persian\n|ndex=053\n|oldjdex=137\n|jdex=139\n|adex=046\n|forme=2\n|form1=Persian\n|form2=Alolan Persian\n|image2=053Persian-Alola.png\n|type1=Normal\n|form2type1=Dark\n|category=Classy Cat\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|height-ftin2=3\'07"\n|height-m2=1.1\n|weight-lbs=70.5\n|weight-kg=32.0\n|weight-lbs2=72.8\n|weight-kg2=33.0\n|abilitylayout=2+2\n|ability1=Limber\n|ability2=Technician\n|abilityd=Unnerve\n|abilitydcaption=Persian\n|ability2-1=Fur Coat\n|ability2-2=Technician\n|abilityd2=Rattled\n|abilityd2caption=Alolan Persian\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsp=2\n|expyield=154\n|oldexp=148\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Yellow\n|formcolors=yes\n|catchrate=90\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=persian\n|generation=1\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Persian\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ペルシアン\'\'\' \'\'Persian\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Meowth}} starting at [[level]] 28.\n\nIn [[Alola]], Persian has a [[regional variant]] that is {{type|Dark}}. It normally evolves from Alolan Meowth when leveled up with high [[friendship]]; however, in [[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!]], it instead evolves from Alolan Meowth starting at [[level]] 28.\n\n==Biology==\nPersian is a large, quadruped, feline Pokémon. Its fur is pale tan with the exception of its black-rimmed ears. It has a short muzzle with a small, black nose, red eyes with slit pupils, rounded ears, a pair of pointed teeth in its upper jaw, and three whiskers on either side of its face. Its thick whiskers are very sensitive to changes in air movements, enabling it to detect its prey by movement alone. In the center of its forehead is a red jewel. Its long tail has a distinctive curl at the end. Persian communicates with body language and holds its tail upright to signal its intention to pounce. It has long legs and three-toed paws with retractable claws. Persian\'s lithe muscles also enable it to walk without making a sound.\n\nPersian normally lives in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Urban Pokémon|towns and cities}}. Although popular for its elegance, it is extremely difficult to raise as a pet due to its fickle and temperamental personality. It will scratch anyone, including its Trainer, with little or no provocation, and has been observed ripping its prey apart for no discernible reason. However, when Persian is yanked by its whiskers, it becomes temporarily docile for unknown reasons. It is popular among rich people and is targeted by hunters for its jewel. In the past, {{m|Pay Day}} was its [[signature move]].\n\nAlolan Persian has a body that is similar to its regular counterpart, but it has blue-gray fur. Its face has a different shape, being larger and more rounded with noticeable jowls. This distinctive face, along with its high-class softer-than-velvet fur coat, is admired by the people of Alola. Its eyes are usually in a half-closed state, and instead of a red forehead jewel, it has a blue jewel. The jewel, though different in appearance, is made of mostly the same material the one on a regular Persian. In behavior, it is described as highly intelligent and having an even higher opinion of itself. It prefers to use underhanded tactics in battle, but its haughty personality causes it to underestimate opponents.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Giovanni Persian.png|250px|left|thumb|Persian in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Madame Pershie.png|250px|right|thumb|Alolan Persian in the anime]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Giovanni\'s Persian]]=====\n{{an|Giovanni}} has a Persian that is his primary Pokémon. It first appeared in \'\'[[EP015|Battle Aboard the St. Anne]]\'\', which also marked the species\' debut. While it is almost always seen at his side, it was only seen battling once, though it proved itself to be an extremely powerful opponent. {{MTR}} seems to be its "rival" as Giovanni\'s "top cat".\n\n=====Other=====\nA Persian that was the leader of a pack of street Meowth (which {{MTR|Team Rocket\'s Meowth}} was also once part of) appeared in \'\'[[EP070|Go West, Young Meowth!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Persian appeared in \'\'[[EP099|The Mandarin Island Miss-Match]]\'\'. {{Ash}} battled the Classy Cat Pokémon, and it was eventually defeated by {{AP|Squirtle}}\'s {{m|Skull Bash}}.\n\nA Persian appeared in \'\'[[AG126|Saved by the Beldum!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Vivica]]. [[Tyson\'s Meowth]] quickly defeated it during the preliminaries of the [[Ever Grande Conference]], but it continued to attack Persian in a fit of rage before being recalled. Persian reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[AG128|Shocks and Bonds]]\'\'.\n\nAn [[Regional variant|Alolan]] Persian, [[nickname]]d \'\'\'Pershie\'\'\' (Japanese: \'\'\'ペルちゃん\'\'\' \'\'Per-chan\'\'), debuted in \'\'[[SM007|That\'s Why the Litten is a Scamp!\u202c]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Madame}}. It stopped {{AP|Litten}} and attacked it, but was later defeated in a rematch. It reappeared in \'\'[[SM083|Dummy, You Shrunk the Kids!]]\'\', where it chased down a shrunken {{Ash}}, {{an|Lillie}}, and {{an|Sophocles}}, but was later defeated by [[Mallow\'s Tsareena]]. It reappeared again in \'\'[[SM099|We Know Where You\'re Going, Eevee!]]\'\', where it chased a [[Sandy|wild Eevee]] and [[Lana\'s Popplio]] until they fell into a river.\n\nAn Alolan Persian appeared in \'\'[[SM077|Guiding an Awakening!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Nanu]]. It was used in Nanu\'s grand trial against Ash, where it was defeated by {{AP|Lycanroc}}\'s {{m|Accelerock}} after it countered its [[Z-Move]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Persian appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[EP015|Battle Aboard the St. Anne]]\'\'.\n\nA Persian appeared in \'\'[[EP044|The Problem with Paras]]\'\'. {{OBP|Lacy|EP044}} found it sleeping in the backyard and decided that it should be [[Cassandra]]\'s company mascot, not Meowth.\n\nA Persian appeared in \'\'[[EP169|Beauty and the Breeder]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Pokémon Breeder}} participating in [[Pokémon Beauty Contest|a Pokémon breeding competition]].\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Persian appeared in \'\'[[AG013|All Things Bright and Beautifly!]]\'\'.\n\nA Coordinator\'s Persian appeared in \'\'[[AG115|Mean With Envy]]\'\'.\n\nA Persian appeared in \'\'[[AG126|Saved by the Beldum!]]\'\' during a flashback, where it led a group of Meowth that left Tyson\'s Meowth behind.\n\nA Coordinator\'s Persian appeared in \'\'[[AG167|What I Did for Love!]]\'\'.\n\nA Persian appeared in \'\'[[M16|Genesect and the Legend Awakened]]\'\' as a resident of [[Pokémon Hills]]. It later battled the [[Genesect Army]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Alolan Persian appeared in \'\'[[SM081|A Young Royal Flame Ignites!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Alolan Persian appeared in \'\'[[SM092|Turning the Other Mask!]]\'\'.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW096|Persian|Ash\'s Pokédex|Persian, the Classy Cat Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Meowth}}. Persian can walk silently thanks to its nimble muscles. It pounces on its prey at lightning speed.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n===In Pokémon Origins===\n[[File:Red Persian PO.png|thumb|250px|Persian in [[Pokémon Origins]]]]\n{{OBP|Red|Origins}} used a Persian in \'\'[[PO04|File 4: Charizard]]\'\' during the [[Indigo Plateau|Pokémon League]] and later to battle with a {{p|Fearow}}.\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Stantler Persian Vulpix PG.png|thumb|left|250px|Persian in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\nA Persian appeared in [[Ecruteak City]] in \'\'[[PG06|The Reawakening]]\'\', during a flashback about the creation of the [[legendary beasts]].\n{{-}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Nanu Grimsley Masters Trailer.png|thumb|250px|Persian (center left) in the [[Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer]]]]\nAn Alolan Persian briefly appeared in the [[Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer]], under the ownership of [[Nanu]]. It was part of a team with its {{pkmn|Trainer}} and [[Grimsley]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Sird Persian.png|thumb|200px|Persian in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[File:Nanu Persian Adventures.png|thumb|200px|left|Alolan Persian in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\nIn \'\'[[PS047|Purrrr-sian]]\'\', {{tc|Super Nerd}} Miles is seen using a Persian to attack {{adv|Yellow}}. It scratches the walls of buildings to create dissonance to disorient Yellow.\n\n[[Sird]] has a Persian as one of her main team members that first appeared in \'\'[[PS277|A Beastly Cold Reception]]\'\'. While it was probably well-trained and helped Sird obtain her position in [[Team Rocket]], it lost to [[Lorelei]]\'s {{p|Slowking}}, forcing her to pursue other means to win the battle.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Persian appeared in \'\'[[PS432|The Final Dimensional Duel II]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PASM01|The Grand Entrance and Delivery Boy Sun]]\'\', a Persian appears with a Meowth in a book owned by a young {{adv|Sun}}, while he was talking to his grandfather on a video chat.\n\nAn [[Regional variant|Alolan]] Persian under the ownership of [[Nanu]] first appeared in \'\'[[PASM03|Pokémon Move Specialist Professor Kukui]]\'\', where it was used to battle against [[Olivia]]\'s {{p|Lycanroc}}.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\n{{OBP|Green|Pocket Monsters}}\'s Meowth evolved into a Persian and [[devolution|devolved]] back into Meowth.\n\nA three-eyed Persian appeared in \'\'[[PM002|Big Battle in the Viridian Forest!!]]\'\'.\n\n===In The Electric Tale of Pikachu manga===\n{{main|Giovanni\'s Persian}}\n{{an|Giovanni}}\'s Persian was seen watching him in \'\'[[ET19|Ash vs. Gary]]\'\' as his anger fades away from remembering the {{pkmn2|giant}} {{p|Slowpoke}} that [[Team Rocket scientists]] created.\n\n===In the How I Became a Pokémon Card manga===\nThe backstory of how Giovanni met Persian is revealed that he rescued it when he was a child.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Persian (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Red Rescue Team and Blue Rescue Team|Pokémon Mystery Dungeon]]: Persian runs the bank at [[Pokémon Square]].\n* {{g|Super Mystery Dungeon}}: The aforementioned Persian returns as an acquaintance of the Duskull from {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time and Explorers of Darkness}} and is recruited once Duskull connects with player.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n====Persian====\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=I|reg1=Kanto|num1=053}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Red|v2=Blue|t2=FFF|entry=Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Yellow|entry=The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Stadium|t=FFF|color=000|entry=It is highly regarded as a pet for its beautiful fur. However, it is extremely temperamental and difficult to keep.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=II|reg1=Johto|num1=137}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Gold|entry=Many adore it for its sophisticated air. However, it will lash out and scratch for little reason.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Silver|entry=Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Crystal|entry=Behind its lithe, elegant appearance lies a barbaric side. It will tear apart its prey on a mere whim.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Stadium 2|t=FFF|color=000|entry=Many adore it for its sophisticated air. However, it will lash out and scratch for little reason.}}\n|}\n|}\n{